## DOMAINS

Product domains represent the key areas your team is working on. Each domain has specific ownership, goals, and guidelines.

### Domain 1 - Analytics & Reporting
**Description:** This domain covers all analytics capabilities, reporting features, dashboard creation, and data visualization tools. It includes both pre-built analytics and custom reporting functionality.

**Special Instructions:**
- Prioritize performance optimization for large datasets (>1M rows)
- Always include export functionality for any new report type
- Ensure all analytics features are accessible via API
- Follow the data governance framework for handling sensitive metrics

### Domain 2 - Integrations & Data Sync
**Description:** Responsible for all third-party integrations, data synchronization, ETL pipelines, and API connectors. Ensures seamless data flow between external tools and our platform.

**Special Instructions:**
- Use webhook-based sync where available to reduce API call volume
- Implement exponential backoff for retry logic on all integrations
- Document rate limits and sync frequency for each integration
- Maintain integration health monitoring dashboard

### Domain 3 - AI & Machine Learning
**Description:** Encompasses all AI-powered features including predictive analytics, natural language processing, automated insights generation, and recommendation systems.

**Special Instructions:**
- All AI features must include explainability/transparency mechanisms
- Model performance metrics must be tracked in production
- Implement fallback logic for when AI confidence is below threshold
- Provide user feedback loops to improve model accuracy

### Domain 4 - User Experience & Interface
**Description:** Covers the product's user interface, interaction design, accessibility, and overall user experience across web and mobile platforms.

**Special Instructions:**
- Follow WCAG 2.1 Level AA accessibility standards
- Mobile-first design approach for all new features
- Conduct usability testing with at least 5 users before major releases
- Maintain design system consistency across all interfaces

### Domain 5 - Platform Infrastructure
**Description:** Backend systems, databases, API architecture, security, authentication, and platform scalability.

**Special Instructions:**
- All APIs must follow RESTful design principles
- Implement rate limiting on all public endpoints
- Security review required for any changes to authentication/authorization
- Document all breaking API changes with 90-day deprecation notice
